Murinye who is also President Emmerson Mnangagwa’s cousin warned the ruling party may lose 2023 polls if lawlessness is not tamed. However, Vice President Constentino Chiwenga, threatened all Chiefs with unspecified action is they continue with utterances similar to the ones made by Chief Murinye. Chief Murinye whose full names are Ephias Munodawafa, recently attacked the ruling ZANU PF and government over anarchy and corruption. He added these are working against President Emmerson Mnangagwa. According to Murinye, the events in government have rendered ordinary people poorer hence the ruling party maybe be ruled out of power in the 2023 polls. Murinye’s utterances shocked Zimbabweans who have always been known for supporting ZANU PF during elections. A few days later Vice President Constentino Chiwenga assembled all Chiefs in Zimbabwe and issued threats against utterances made by Chief Murinye. Take a listen to this report by George Mhango…  --Channel Africa--